I"ÿ<h2 id="learning-goals">Learning Goals</h2>

<p>Students will:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Research and articulate different programming principles</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="part-1-research-10-mins">Part 1: Research (10 mins)</h2>

<p>Count off into groups of 6.
Each group of 1-6 will go their separate ways for now, but will come back together later. Remember who your group is, then go to your topic group (all the 1â€™s should be together, 5â€™s together, etc.)</p>

<p>For each of the following topics, work with your topic group to research the following:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Code Smells</li>
  <li>Single Responsibility Principle</li>
  <li>Abstraction</li>
  <li>Encapsulation</li>
  <li>Law of Demeter</li>
  <li>DRY/YAGNI</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="part-2-solidify--communicate-15-mins">Part 2: Solidify &amp; Communicate (15 mins)</h2>

<p>Each group should make a Chart Paper summarizing the assigned principle and why it is important.
Examples, analogies, and diagrams are encouraged!</p>

<h2 id="part-3-share-20-mins">Part 3: Share (20 mins)</h2>

<p>Come back together with your 1-6 group. Each member should have researched a different topic. You are now the expert - take 2 minutes to share the following on your topic:</p>

<ol>
  <li>What is it?</li>
  <li>Why is it important?</li>
</ol>
